prism

Class UndefinedConstants

  • java.lang.Object
    • prism.UndefinedConstants

  • public class UndefinedConstants
extends java.lang.Object
    Class to handle the undefined constants in model and/or properties file. This may not be *all* of the constants in the file(s); it may be just the ones that are required to execute model checking or some other task. Really, the main purpose of this class is to manage an "experiment", i.e. to iterate through several different values of one or more constants, but this includes the special case where all undefined constants are given a single value.

        Construct information about undefined constants from a model and/or properties file. If either is not required, it can be left as null. If justLabels is false, all constants, whether used or not, are assumed to be required to be provided. If justLabels is true, only properties file constants that are needed for labels are.

        public boolean defineConstant(java.lang.String name,
                              java.lang.String val)
                       throws PrismException
        Define value for a single undefined constant. Returns whether or not an existing definition was overwritten. Actually just helper method for more general method below. The method initialiseIterators must be called after all constants are defined.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the constant.
        val - The value to be assigned.
        Returns:
        True if the constant was defined before.
        Throws:
        PrismException

      • defineConstant

        public boolean defineConstant(java.lang.String name,
                              java.lang.String sl,
                              java.lang.String sh,
                              java.lang.String ss)
                       throws PrismException
        Define value for a single undefined constant. Returns whether or not an existing definition was overwritten. The method initialiseIterators must be called after all constants are defined.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the constant.
        sl - If sh are ss are null, this is the value to be assigned. Otherwise, it is the lower bound for the range.
        sh - The upper bound for the range.
        ss - The step for the values. Null means 1.
        Returns:
        True if the constant was defined before.
        Throws:
        PrismException

      • defineConstant

        public boolean defineConstant(java.lang.String name,
                              java.lang.String sl,
                              java.lang.String sh,
                              java.lang.String ss,
                              boolean useAll)
                       throws PrismException
        Define value for a single undefined constant. Returns whether or not an existing definition was overwritten. The method initialiseIterators must be called after all constants are defined.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the constant.
        sl - If sh are ss are null, this is the value to be assigned. Otherwise, it is the lower bound for the range.
        sh - The upper bound for the range.
        ss - The step for the values. Null means 1.
        useAll - If true, throw an exception if name does not need to be defined
        Returns:
        True if the constant was defined before.
        Throws:
        PrismException
